######### MS-DOS commands in Window #####
dir : shows a list of all files in the current directories
cd .. : Changes the directory to indicated directory
cd \ : Chages directory to root directory (often C)
copy : Copies files to another location
del filename : Deletes one or more files
find : Searches for text in files
mkdir directory :  Creates a new directory
ren oldname newname : Renames a file
help : Displays all the commands with brief description
help command : Displays extensive help for the indicated commands

Hardware abstraction layer (HAL) : software that handles all of the communiation between hardware and kernel.
Kernel : the core of the operating system and has control over the entire computer.
Device drivers : specialized software that acts as a translator between an operating system (OS) and hardware devices, allowing them to communicate and function properly.
BIOS : BIOS, or Basic Input/Output System, is software stored on a small memory chip, also known as firmware.
UEFI : Unified Extensible Firmware Interface (UEFI) is a modern, 64-bit firmware interface that acts as a faster, more secure, and feature-rich replacement for traditional Legacy BIOS.

Installed application runs in user mode and operating system code runs in kernel mode.

Process : A process is any program that is currently executing.
Thread : A thread is a part of the process that can be executed.
*** The processor performs calculation on threads. ***
*** Multiple threads can be executed at the same time. ***
